<description>

The Manage Scheduler Jobs page displays a table of all batch jobs with columns for Job Name, Is Active (toggle), CRON Expression, Previous Run Status (Success/Failed with start/end times), Next Run Time, Currently Running indicator, and action buttons. Jobs include Apply Annual Fee, Add Accrual Transactions, Apply Penalty to Overdue Loans, Update Loan Summary, Post Interest for Savings, Transfer Fees, and Generate Loan Loss Provisioning. Each job can be toggled active/inactive and its CRON expression edited. A global Start/Stop scheduler toggle controls whether all scheduled jobs execute.

The Global Configuration page displays a table of system-wide feature flags with columns for Configuration Name, Enabled (toggle), Value, and Description. Key settings include maker-checker (4-eyes approval), reschedule-future-repayments, allow-transactions-on-non-workingday, reschedule-repayments-on-holidays, savings-interest-posting-current-period-end, financial-year-beginning-month, and meetings-mandatory-for-jlg-loans.

The Manage Codes page lists all code lists (Client Type, Gender, Address Type, Loan Purpose, etc.) with Name and Is System Defined columns. Clicking a code opens its values for adding, editing, reordering, and deactivating entries that populate dropdown options throughout the system.

The Manage Data Tables page lists custom data tables that extend core entities (m_client, m_group, m_loan, m_office, m_saving_account, m_product_loan, m_savings_product) with custom fields. The Create form includes Data Table Name, Application Table Name dropdown, Multi Row checkbox, and column definitions — each with Name, Type (string, number, boolean, decimal, date, datetime, text, dropdown), Length, Is Mandatory, and Is Unique checkboxes.

The Audit Trails page displays all system actions with columns for Action Name, Entity Name, Resource ID, Maker, Made On Date, Checker, Checked On Date, Processing Result (Pending, Approved, Rejected), Office Name, and Client/Loan/Savings details. Filters allow searching by Action Name, Entity Name, Resource ID, Maker ID, Checker ID, Office, and Date Range. When maker-checker is enabled, pending commands appear with Approve and Reject buttons.

---


</description>

<workflows>
WF-001 | Toggle Scheduler Execution (Start/Stop Scheduler) | actor: Administrator | branch: none | terminal: Scheduler_Enabled | on_success: enables or disables execution of all scheduled jobs globally
WF-002 | Edit CRON (row action) | actor: Administrator | branch: none | terminal: Edit CRON | on_success: persists edited CRON expression for the job
WF-003 | Toggle Job Active (row action) | actor: Administrator | branch: none | terminal: Toggle Active | on_success: toggles Is_Active for the job
WF-004 | Toggle Job Active (inline) | actor: Administrator | branch: none | terminal: Is_Active | on_success: toggles Is_Active for the job
WF-005 | Update CRON Expression (inline edit) | actor: Administrator | branch: none | terminal: CRON_Expression | on_success: updates the job's schedule; editable per job (inline or modal)
WF-006 | Run Job Now (row action) | actor: Administrator | branch: none | terminal: Run Now | on_success: queues immediate execution of the selected job
WF-007 | View Job Run History (row action) | actor: Administrator | branch: none | terminal: View Run History | on_success: navigates to job run history for the selected job
WF-008 | Toggle Global Configuration Enabled (inline) | actor: Administrator | branch: none | terminal: Enabled | on_success: toggles the feature flag or configuration entry for the system
WF-009 | Edit Global Configuration (row action) | actor: Administrator | branch: none | terminal: Edit | on_success: persists the configuration value for the entry
WF-010 | Update Global Configuration Value (inline) | actor: Administrator | branch: none | terminal: Value | on_success: persists the configuration value for the entry
WF-011 | Open Code List | actor: Administrator | branch: none | terminal: Open Code | on_success: opens Manage_Code_Values for the selected code list
WF-012 | Add Value to Code List | actor: Administrator | branch: none | terminal: Add Value | on_success: adds a new value row to the code list
WF-013 | Save Changes to Code List | actor: Administrator | branch: none | terminal: Save Changes | on_success: persists edits, order changes, and active state toggles
WF-014 | Edit Custom Data Table (row action) | actor: Administrator | branch: none | terminal: Edit | on_success: opens Create_Data_Table_Form in edit mode for the selected custom table
WF-015 | Create Custom Data Table | actor: Administrator | branch: none | terminal: Create | on_success: creates the custom data table and associated columns
WF-016 | Cancel Create Custom Data Table | actor: Administrator | branch: none | terminal: Cancel | on_success: cancels creation and returns to Manage Data Tables list
WF-017 | View Audit Entry Details | actor: Administrator | branch: none | terminal: View Details | on_success: opens audit entry details
WF-018 | Approve Pending Command | actor: Administrator | branch: Processing Result == Pending AND maker-checker (4-eyes approval) feature flag enabled | terminal: Approve | on_success: marks the pending command as Approved and triggers post-approve processing
WF-019 | Reject Pending Command with Reason | actor: Administrator | branch: Processing Result == Pending AND maker-checker (4-eyes approval) feature flag enabled | terminal: Reject | on_success: marks the pending command as Rejected and records the rejection reason
</workflows>

